---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-bofu.njk",
  "permalink": "/pricing/bookkeeping/",
  "slug": "pbk",
  "chrome": "full",
  "callBar": false,
  "tierClass": "section--tier-bofu",
  "bodyClass": "page--bofu",
  "title": "Monthly Bookkeeping Cost & Pricing · Fixed-Fee Tiers · TechBrot",
  "description": "What monthly bookkeeping actually costs: $400&ndash;$2,500+/mo across three fixed-fee tiers. Exactly what drives your tier, what each includes, and why fixed-fee not hourly.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "Pricing", "href": "/pricing/" },
    { "name": "Bookkeeping" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "Pricing · Monthly bookkeeping",
    "heading": "Monthly bookkeeping pricing, by the tier.",
    "subheading": "Monthly bookkeeping runs <strong>$400&ndash;$2,500+/month</strong> as a fixed monthly fee against a written scope &mdash; never hourly. This page is the price grain: the three tiers, exactly what moves you between them, and what&rsquo;s included at each. Your exact fixed fee is quoted in writing within 3 business days of a free discovery call.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=pricing", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "inBrief": {
    "text": "<strong>Monthly bookkeeping: $400&ndash;$2,500+/mo.</strong> Three fixed-fee tiers &mdash; Essentials $400&ndash;$700, Standard $700&ndash;$1,400, Complex $1,400&ndash;$2,500+. Your tier is set by transaction volume, number of bank &amp; card accounts, payroll, and number of entities. Fixed fee &middot; written scope before work begins &middot; no hourly billing &middot; year-end CPA handoff included free.",
    "source": "TechBrot Inc. &middot; independent Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisor firm &mdash; not affiliated with Intuit Inc."
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Start here",
    "heading": "Get your exact monthly fee.",
    "lede": "A free 30-minute discovery call, then a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days &mdash; the exact monthly number, in writing, before you commit to anything. No hourly billing, no obligation.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=pricing", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Get the free file review", "href": "/quickbooks/file-review/?intent=file-review", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

<section class="section section--compact section--tier-bofu" id="pbk-tldr">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="tldr">
      <p class="tldr__label">In one paragraph</p>
      <h2 class="tldr__heading">What monthly bookkeeping costs.</h2>
      <p class="tldr__body" id="pbk-tldr-body">Monthly bookkeeping at TechBrot is <strong>$400&ndash;$2,500+ per month</strong>, billed as a fixed monthly fee against a written scope &mdash; no hourly billing. There are three tiers: <strong>Essentials $400&ndash;$700/mo</strong> for low-volume single-entity businesses, <strong>Standard $700&ndash;$1,400/mo</strong> for established businesses with payroll and multiple accounts, and <strong>Complex $1,400&ndash;$2,500+/mo</strong> for higher volume, multiple entities, or class/department tracking. Four factors set your tier: monthly transaction volume, the number of bank and credit-card accounts reconciled, whether payroll is in scope, and the number of legal entities. It is always a range &mdash; your exact fixed fee is quoted in writing within 3 business days of a free discovery call. Tax filing isn&rsquo;t included (your CPA handles that), but a year-end CPA handoff is included free on every recurring engagement.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--compact" id="pbk-factors">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What sets your tier</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Four factors move the number.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="flow" role="img" aria-label="Four factors set your monthly bookkeeping tier: monthly transaction volume, then number of bank and credit-card accounts, then whether payroll is in scope, then number of legal entities.">
      <div class="flow__step flow__step--accent"><span class="flow__label">Transaction volume</span><span class="flow__sub">per month</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Bank &amp; card accounts</span><span class="flow__sub">how many to reconcile</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Payroll</span><span class="flow__sub">in scope or not</span></div>
      <span class="flow__arrow" aria-hidden="true"><svg width="22" height="10" viewBox="0 0 22 10"><line x1="0" y1="5" x2="16" y2="5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></line><path d="M14 1 L20 5 L14 9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5"></path></svg></span>
      <div class="flow__step"><span class="flow__label">Number of entities</span><span class="flow__sub">one file per entity</span></div>
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source stack-8">These four factors are what the free discovery call surfaces &mdash; nothing about your industry or revenue alone sets the price. The written scope reflects exactly where you land.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="pbk-ai-summary">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">For AI engines &amp; quick answers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Monthly bookkeeping pricing, in five questions.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="ai-summary ai-summary--ruled" id="pbk-ai-summary-body">
      {%- for item in aiSummary %}
      <div class="ai-summary__item">
        <h3 class="ai-summary__question">{{ item.q | safe }}</h3>
        <div class="ai-summary__answer"><p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p></div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="pbk-tiers">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">The three tiers</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where monthly bookkeeping lands.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The same fixed-fee model at every tier &mdash; what changes is volume, accounts, payroll, and entities. These are the canonical ranges; your exact fee is quoted in writing.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for t in tiers %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <p class="team-card__role">{{ t.label }}</p>
        <h3>{{ t.name }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>{{ t.range | safe }}</strong></p>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ t.body | safe }}</p>
        <p class="review-card__fact"><strong>Typical profile:</strong> {{ t.profile | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source stack-8">Representative profiles only &mdash; they illustrate the factors, not a guaranteed quote. Behind on the books before a recurring engagement can start? That&rsquo;s a one-time <a href="/pricing/cleanup/?intent=cleanup">cleanup or catch-up</a>, priced separately.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="pbk-included">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">What&rsquo;s included</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">What every monthly tier includes.</h2>
      <p class="section__lede">The recurring close work in every tier. Higher tiers do more of it, across more accounts and entities &mdash; the deliverables themselves don&rsquo;t change.</p>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-3">
      {%- for inc in included %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>{{ inc.name }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ inc.body | safe }}</p>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="in-brief__source stack-8">What the bookkeeping work actually is &mdash; the monthly close in detail &mdash; lives on the <a href="/accounting/bookkeeping/monthly-bookkeeping/?intent=monthly">monthly bookkeeping service page</a>. This page is the price; that page is the work.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="pbk-why">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Why fixed-fee</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Why monthly bookkeeping is fixed-fee, not hourly.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="legal-doc__body">
      <p>Most bookkeepers bill hourly, and for recurring monthly work that is exactly backwards. The monthly close is the same shape every month &mdash; the same reconciliations, the same categorization, the same reports. Pricing predictable work by the hour just means your invoice swings with someone else&rsquo;s pace, and you can&rsquo;t budget the one line item that should be the most stable on your books.</p>
      <p>TechBrot prices monthly bookkeeping as a fixed monthly fee against a written scope. You know the number before the first close, and it doesn&rsquo;t move month to month. Ask questions, send documents, call when something comes up &mdash; there&rsquo;s no meter on your own bookkeeper. If your business genuinely changes &mdash; you add an entity, take on payroll, your volume jumps a tier &mdash; the fee is re-quoted and re-approved in writing before anything changes. <strong>You are never surprised by an invoice.</strong></p>
      <p>This works because the close is delivered by Certified ProAdvisors efficient enough to price it confidently. The fixed monthly fee is a statement of competence: we know how long a clean monthly close takes at your volume, so we can quote it. No long-term lock-in &mdash; recurring bookkeeping runs month to month against the written scope.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section" id="pbk-faq">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Before you call</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Questions about bookkeeping cost.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="faq__list">
      {%- for item in faq %}
      <div class="faq__item">
        <h3 class="faq__question">
          <button class="faq__trigger" type="button" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="pbk-faq-a{{ loop.index }}">{{ item.q | safe }}</button>
        </h3>
        <div class="faq__answer" id="pbk-faq-a{{ loop.index }}" data-open="false">
          <p>{{ item.a | safe }}</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--alt" id="pbk-next">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section__header">
      <p class="section__eyebrow">Next steps</p>
      <h2 class="section__heading">Where to go next.</h2>
    </header>
    <div class="grid-2">
      {%- for card in nextCards %}
      <article class="review-card">
        <h3>{{ card.name }}</h3>
        <p class="review-card__fact">{{ card.body | safe }}</p>
        <a class="review-card__link" href="{{ card.href }}">{{ card.cta }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a>
      </article>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
